<h1><span class="mw-headline" id="Testsuite"> Testsuite </span></h1>
<p>We have a repository with lots of small test programs along with a testing driver script in:
</p>
<pre><a class="external free" href="http://pp.info.uni-karlsruhe.de/git/firm-testsuite.git">http://pp.info.uni-karlsruhe.de/git/firm-testsuite.git</a>
(cgit at <a class="external free" href="http://pp.info.uni-karlsruhe.de/git/firm-testsuite/">http://pp.info.uni-karlsruhe.de/git/firm-testsuite/</a>)
</pre>
<h1><span class="mw-headline" id="Buildbot"> Buildbot </span></h1>
<p>We also started using buildbot for automatically running tests on pushs. If you are on the internal IPD Network you can find it here:
</p>
<pre><a class="external free" href="http://i44sun3.info.uni-karlsruhe.de:8010/">http://i44sun3.info.uni-karlsruhe.de:8010/</a>
</pre>
<p>If you have access to the firm account then you can edit the config like this:
</p>
<pre>ssh firm@i44sun3
cd /data1/firm/buildbot
. nolimits.sh
. bin/activate
vi master/master.cfg
(buildbot checkconfig master)
buildbot reconfig master
</pre>

